And The means by which a horse is treated, consisting in what are termed taDomiyrN and HanocN 
[explained in the second paragraph {1} 
of art. Dmr 
and the first {1} 
of art. Hnc]: and the means by which a young woman, or female slave, is treated in order that she may become fat: and also applied to milk; because they used to effect the tDmyr of horses by the drinking of milk, and to treat therewith the young woman, or female slave: and it is likewise called qafiy-apN; because she has it given to her in preference, like as the guest has, and the child. (Ṣ, TA.)
